HEADWORD: Corroval
<hw>Cor*ro"val</hw> <pr>(kr-r?"v<it>a</it>l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
dark brown substance of vegetable origin, allied to curare, and used by
the natives of New Granada as an arrow poison.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corrovaline</ent>⟦br⟧
